                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d229">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6131/330: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_BWC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-13T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 13, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 13—6:34 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>281. I signed today at 1 o’clock with <persName corresp="#p_LMM1"
                        >Litvinov</persName> notes and letters and will release notes to press at 5
                    p.m., this afternoon, Saturday July 13th (10 a.m., Washington time). I venture
                    to suggest that in issuing the text of the identic notes the Department should
                    at the same time make the statement made in the fifth paragraph of my 275, July
                    11, 5 p.m. I will make available to the press on July 15, 5 p.m. (10 a.m.
                    Washington time) the text of my letter to <persName corresp="#p_LMM1"
                        >Litvinov</persName> dated July 11 and of <persName corresp="#p_LMM1"
                        >Litvinov</persName>’s reply dated July 15th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
